column7: and agricultural land surrounds our site. Chavez is located in\r\rDistrict Governing Boarda rural neighborhood of parents and community members who take pride in their school.\rRuben MendozaBoard President\rArea 3\rStaff at Chavez work together to meet the needs of every student. Every grade level meets in\rrubenmendoza@maderausd.org\rProfessional Learning Communities in order to discuss current student data and to make decisions\r\rabout best practices. These meetings are scheduled weekly on Tuesdays and Thursdays during the\rBrent FernandesBoard Clerk\rstaff development portion of our minimum day.  Many teams of teachers utilize additional time Area 7\rbrentfernandes@maderausd.orgafter the school day to work together to plan and provide students with quality instruction.\r\rRay G. SeibertArea 1Students deploy among their own grade level to receive scaffolded yet rigorous reading instruction\rrayseibert@maderausd.org\rin grade 4-6. Students in grades K-3 receive guided reading instruction to meet their individual and\r\rspecific needs.  Students with intensive needs meet in small groups with the RtI Reading Specialist.\rEd McIntyreArea 2\rAll groups are adjusted as students progress. COST and Student Study Team (SST) meetings with\redmcintyre@maderausd.org\rteachers and parents are held as needed in order to discuss student needs and progress. These\rJoetta FleakArea 4meetings include discussions in regards to all strategies/interventions provided for our students\rjoettafleak@maderausd.organd the necessary next steps needed to meet their needs. Our special-needs students receive\r\rsupportingeneraleducationclassroomsbyhighlyqualifiedSpecialEdTeachersand\rLucy SalazarArea 5\rParaprofessionals.\rlucysalazar@maderausd.org\r\r\rParents at Chavez are actively involved in the education of their children. This is demonstrated by\rJ. Gordon KennedyArea 6\rtheir personal involvement

column13: \rcommon core aligned units of instruction.
